node.text: Hunny sometimes you need a little drinky drink so you can thinky think! I’m so excited to partner with @amazonprimevideo  for their new series “Prime Pairings”. I make delicious food that you can make and enjoy while watching your favorite @amazonprimevideo shows!! Watch me make  stuffed Bacon Bbq Burgers, and a Compound V cocktail, to eat while I watch one of my favorite amazon prime series @theboystvthis !! Be sure to check it out!! Head on over to @amazonprimevideo  YouTube channel to get this particular full recipe, and more recipes! Link in bio!!

node.text: Hey y’all!! Listen .. I know I look a mess ..but hunny.. this cake don’t!! It’s one of my favorite dessert recipes in my cookbook! Red velvet pound cake with cream cheese glaze! It’s perfect to eat while you watch our new podcast @thisisgrownfolksbusiness  on Sunday nights at 7 pm!! Enter the code “Podcast” to  get 50% off of my cookbooks today!! And be sure to tune in tomorrow night, and follow @thisisgrownfolksbusiness  too! Link in bio to books! Podcast can be watched on my channel and also available on Apple, Spotify or wherever you listen to ya podcast mmkay!  Ps.. ima church gurl gone wild .. y’all keep praying for me 🤦🏾‍♀️😩😂

node.text: #AD Chile…. you know I love to keep it real with y’all and sometimes that means showing the good and the bad when it comes to cooking! Listen hunny, sometimes a little burn doesn’t mean it still can’t be Sopped Up! With that being said, if something goes wrong, it’s always an easy fix! Hunny, My mama always taught me how to take a lickin’ and keep on tickin..so, no matter what, have no shame in your game in the kitchen! This is why I’m takin the #NoShame challenge with @icantbelieveitsnotbutter. It has less than 70% less saturated fat than butter with less calories and it’s gluten free!! Ya’ll remember to be kind to yourself, and no matter what, keep cooking! #NotButterNotSorry #icantbelieveitsnotbutter

node.text: #AD Yall, this has been a year, with that being said we could all use something sweet right about now, so I wanted to do something sweet and easy for Falloween! Making candy apples is so simple, and it’s a southern staple that I love! These  cute Boo Baskets are perfect to make with kids and share with close friends and family! Which is why I love @KrogerCo!  I can rely on them for all of my seasonal candy and décor needs, plus fresh foods and snacks! Hunny, Aint nothin spooky about that!! Plus Kroger makes it so easy with free pickup and digital coupons, making it a one stop shop for all things spooky, sticky, and sweet!

node.text:
#Ad .. Hey y’all!  I am so excited, because it’s that time of year! Sweet Vidalia Onions are FINALLY in season! The distinct flavor that comes from a Vidalia onion is the perfect foodie fix, that this southern girl could use right now! In the midst of everything going around us, there is nothing more comforting than a sweet, delicious, deep fried @Vidaliaonion1 blooming onion! I decided to top mine with cheesy queso,  seasoned ground beef and homemade salsa! This is so simple and quick, and the taste is even better! Check out the full written recipe below!  #onlyvidalia 
Recipe. 
Ingredients: •1 Large Vidalia Onion •2 cups self rising flour ( all purpose is ok too) •
•Seasoning of choice ( such as seasoning salt) •1/2 lb Ground beef or protein of choice •Melted Queso cheese •Prepared Salsa •Cooking oil •1/2  milk •1 egg ( scrambled in a bowl) •Taco seasoning 
Instructions:
Fill a deep fryer or deep pot with cooking oil halfway.  Do not fill to the top, because the oil will rise once you place the onion inside. Preheat oil to 375 degrees if using a fryer. 
To prepare onion:
•Remove the skin of the onion.. and remove the top with a sharp knife. •Lay the onion flat side down on a clean surface or cutting board •Take a sharp knife and cut slices on the side of the onion. Be sure to cut deep enough to separate the onion.. but not deep enough to completely remove the petals. •Fan the onion out a bit once it is cut to separate the petals. * Add flour to bowl and seasonings of choice * Add milk in splashes to the flour to create little crumbles into the flour.
* Pour egg mixture on top of onion and coat with seasoning flour. Set aside for a few minutes
* Preheat a large skillet, and add ground beef or meat of choice to the skillet; cook until desired temperature. Strain meat and place back into skillet. * Sprinkle taco seasoning over meat and mix together; set aside.
* Place onion into hot oil and cook for 6-7 minutes or until crispy golden brown. * Remove onion once cooked, and place on paper towel to strain grease. * Top with queso cheese, salsa .. and any additonal toppings you’d like!  #tacotuesday

node.title: Taco style Fried Blooming Vidalia Onion

node.text:
Hey y’all! I’m so excited about the new series PANIC! 

It was so engaging  and  exciting to watch! Now listen, before you snuggle up on the sofa and binge watch the new series.. I want you to make my delicious Sweet and spicy Joe sliders, with a coke slushy! These sliders were bomb yall! So head on over to prime pairings ( click the link in my bio) to see how I made them, and don’t forget to watch @paniconprime  available now on @amazonprimevideo !!! Link in my bio for the full recipe and video, or head on over to @amazonprimevideo  YouTube channel and check it out!

node.text:
Listen!!!!! “ We may not take a lot of pics together, but we friends in real life” -@mrskevonstage 😂😂😂.. y’all today is @mrskevonstage  bday!!!!!!!! This woman is the epitome of style and grace!!! She is a testimony, that God still answers prayers, because  I prayed for a friendship like ours! Words cannot express how grateful I am that we met!! Listen, if you don’t believe that great, caring, and loving ppl still exist in life, I’m here to tell you that you’re wrong. Because I am a living witness, after meeting this woman and her family, that they do. It has been such a joy, Melissa.. and I thank God for our friendship daily! Girlfriend, you are exceptional! And it’s such a pleasure being your friend! Thank you for all that you do, the way that you pour, the way that you give, and the way that you love and care, will never go Un noticed!, may God richly bless you, always, and forever! Y’all go and wish @mrskevonstage a HAPPY BURFDAY!!!! Buy her merch too! 

PS..
Get you some friends that will drank  port wine and listen to Kirk Franklin at the same time!! 😂😂

Did y’all know that I posted a new recipe the other day on my channel ?? Mmhm.. sholl did. And it’s perfect for summer!! Simple and easy! Because we added parsley it’s healthy... because parsley is green.. and my mama said food that’s green is healthy. #period .. 

Thank you @texaspetesauces !! I had a blast making this!! Link in my bio to my youtube channel guys! And be sure to subscribe y’all! #food #texaspete #youtube

node.text: Good Mawnin!! Many of you have been asking for a  spaghetti recipe! I have two on my channel already! Yes, both are #soppedup ..pick ya poison! 🤷🏽‍♀️😂.. NEW recipes dropping  on my channel next week!! I’m so excited to be back in the kitchen, with a ton of new recipes! It’s about to be a good #jukejointsumma ... So, if you haven’t subscribed to my channel already, click the link in my bio!! We are almost at 1 million subscribers!!! Thank you, thank you, thank you!!Wow! My heart is full❤️.. God bless all of you!! And these are our morning church announcements. Have a good weekend y’all!

node.text: Chile, I find some of the best cuts of meat here in the sunny jungle, aka LA.. no matter where I live, ima always cook like I’m back home. I couldn’t resist these big ole meaty oxtails in the store.. so, I grabbed  them and made them just like the recipe that I already have on my channel, and it was everything that I needed yesterday.. this dinner was better than some of y’all relationships. But I digress... yes my oxtail recipe is already on my channel.. this recipe is not the Jamaican way, it’s not the traditional southern way.. it’s the #Soppedup way.  Period

node.text: #fathersdaycookout.. Have y’all tried my potato salad recipe? Now y’all know... if the tata salad don’t have paprika and chopped eggs sprinkled on top for decoration.. It ain’t right and you betta not eat it! 🤷🏽‍♀️😂.. Listen... I have all the tricks, secret ingredients and tips to make GOOD traditional southern style potato salad.. you don’t need onion, bell pepper, and celery either.. trust me.. once you make it this way.. you wont go back! Be sure to check out my seafood potato salad recipe too!! Now , that one is definitely a game changer! Whew! It’s potato salad crack! One of my favorite things to eat is potato salad with baked beans ... yup I have a good baked beans recipe too.. Check previous post 👉🏾.. both recipes are already on my channel! Link in bio!! Make it for Father’s Day!! #youtube #food

node.text: #happyjuneteenth ..my southern BBQ baked beans recipe is the only recipe you will need to take to the festivities!! Yes, ground beef goes into baked beans!!!! Listen hunny, if you don’t put ground beef in your baked beans... well, you’re just not doing it right 🤷🏽‍♀️.. it’s the only way, it’s the southern way... period....the recipe is on my channel already! It’s an oldie, but goodie! Grab the strawberry soda, turn on some Johnny Taylor, Bobby Womack, Betty Wright, or Shirley Brown.. and enjoy ya self today!

node.text: It’s summa summa summa time!! And it’s hotter than a  3 dollar pistol outside chile! Hunny, one day @youvegtmel  and I were sitting outside running our mouth.. and she talked about craving a seafood Caesar salad.. Long story short, I told her I’d make one, test the recipe to see if it’s good... and then I’ll make it again for her Lol!! I did just that.. and it turned out fantastic!!! Loaded seafood Caesar salad... crab, shrimp, bacon, salmon, fresh lemon.. fresh parmesan.. this is the way I would serve a salad in a juke joint... it met all of my needs and more! Perfect way to cool down for the summa time! @youvegtmel , thank you for sharing all of your pregnancy cravings!! So far they’ve been a hit! 😂 y’all can thank her for this one! It’s coming to my channel!! I’m so excited to share all the new recipes!
